<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="robert" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Calling Vulcan Init Procedures</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Calling Vulcan Init Procedures</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Because support for Init Procedures is still missing you must add a special section of code to your program.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If your app does not use one of the SDK assemblies you may have to delete on or more of these lines.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">PROCEDURE AppInit()</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">VulcanLoader.InitVulcan()</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">TypeOf(Vulcan.VO.DataWindow):Assembly:GetType(&quot;VulcanVOGUIClasses.Functions&quot;):GetMethod(&quot;$Init1&quot;):Invoke(NULL,NULL)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">TypeOf(Vulcan.VO.DbServer):Assembly:GetType(&quot;VulcanVORDDClasses.Functions&quot;):GetMethod(&quot;$Init1&quot;):Invoke(NULL,NULL)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">TypeOf(Vulcan.VO.FieldSpec):Assembly:GetType(&quot;VulcanVOSystemClasses.Functions&quot;):GetMethod(&quot;$Init1&quot;):Invoke(NULL,NULL)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">TypeOf(Vulcan.VO.LogFile):Assembly:GetType(&quot;VulcanVOWin32APILibrary.Functions&quot;):GetMethod(&quot;$Init1&quot;):Invoke(NULL,NULL)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">TypeOf(Vulcan.ErrorDialog):Assembly:GetType(&quot;VulcanRTFuncs.Functions&quot;):GetMethod(&quot;$Init1&quot;):Invoke(NULL,NULL)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">TypeOf(Vulcan.VO.DataWindow):Assembly:GetType(&quot;VulcanVOGUIClasses.Functions&quot;):GetMethod(&quot;$Init3&quot;):Invoke(NULL,NULL)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">CLASS VulcanLoader</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">STATIC METHOD InitVulcan() AS VOID</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">LOCAL t AS Type</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">t := typeof(VulcanLoader)</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">LOCAL mi AS System.Reflection.MethodInfo</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">mi := t:GetMethod( &quot;InitVulcan&quot; )</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">Vulcan.Runtime.State.AppModule := mi:Module</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">END CLASS</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">And in the beginning of Start() add a simple call before doing anything else:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">AppInit()</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In a future build this (kind of) code will be automatically generated by the compiler when running in BYOR mode.</text></para>
  </body>
